Sentencas: In this work, W-containing Sr1-xBaxFe0.75W0.25O3-delta (x = 0, 0.5, 1) perovskite-related oxides have been for the first time evaluated in terms of their possible application as anode materials in solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Evaluation of W-containing Sr1-xBaxFe0.75W0.25O3-δ (x=0, 0.5, 1) anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Crystal structure, thermal expansion coefficient, transport properties, oxygen content, chemical compatibility in relation to ceria-based electrolyte, and stability of the materials in reducing atmospheres have been studied.
Titulo: Evaluation of W-containing Sr1-xBaxFe0.75W0.25O3-δ (x=0, 0.5, 1) anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It was found that SrFe0.75W0.25O3-delta and Sr0.5Ba0.5Fe0.75W0.25O3-delta oxides show simple perovskite-type structure with cubic Pm-3m symmetry, while BaFe0.75W0.25O3-delta exhibits hexagonal P6(3)/mmc structure.
Titulo: Evaluation of W-containing Sr1-xBaxFe0.75W0.25O3-δ (x=0, 0.5, 1) anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Small grains (-2 mu m) can be obtained for SrFe0.75W0.25O3-delta compound with very simple, high-temperature synthesis process in air.
Titulo: Evaluation of W-containing Sr1-xBaxFe0.75W0.25O3-δ (x=0, 0.5, 1) anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Large oxygen nonstoichiometry changes of Delta delta approximate to 0.36 were observed for SrFe0.75W0.25O3-delta oxide upon heating in 5 vol.% H-2 in argon.
Titulo: Evaluation of W-containing Sr1-xBaxFe0.75W0.25O3-δ (x=0, 0.5, 1) anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Seebeck coefficient and electrical conductivity measurements revealed that SrFe0.75W0.25O3-delta oxide exhibits p-type conductivity in air and n-type conductivity under reducing conditions.
Titulo: Evaluation of W-containing Sr1-xBaxFe0.75W0.25O3-δ (x=0, 0.5, 1) anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This oxide presents relatively good chemical compatibility in relation to Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 electrolyte, and chemical stability in 5 vol.% H-2 in argon up to at least 800 degrees C. Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy studies for SrFe0.75W0.25O3-delta-based cells conducted in pure hydrogen and CH4 indicated the possibility of the application of SrFe0.75W0.25O3-delta as the anode material in SOFCs.
Titulo: Evaluation of W-containing Sr1-xBaxFe0.75W0.25O3-δ (x=0, 0.5, 1) anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells
